{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Culture of the Republic of Azerbaijan |nativename = Azərbaycan Respublikasının Mədəniyyət Nazirliyi |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = Coat of arms of Azerbaijan.svg |seal_width = 120px |seal_caption = Coat of Arms of Azerbaijan |formed = May, 1953 |date1 = |date1_name = |date2 = |date2_name = |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = |headquarters = Azadliq Avenue 1, [[Government House, Baku|Government House]] [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan Republic]] AZ1000 |latd = |latm = |lats = |latNS = |longd = |longm = |longs = |longEW = |employees = |budget = |chief1_name = [[Abulfaz Garayev]] |chief1_position = Minister |chief2_name = [[Vagif Aliyev]] |chief2_position = First Deputy Minister |chief3_name = Sevda Mammadaliyeva |chief3_position = Deputy Minister |chief4_name = [[Rafig Bayramov]] |chief4_position = Deputy Minister |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = [http://www.culture.gov.az www.culture.gov.az] |footnotes = }}
The '''Ministry of Culture of Azerbaijan Republic''' ({{lang-az|Azərbaycan Respublikasının Mədəniyyət Nazirliyi}}) is a [[governmental agency]] within the [[Cabinet of Azerbaijan]] in charge of regulation of the activities and promotion of [[Culture of Azerbaijan|Azerbaijani culture]]. The ministry is headed by [[Abulfaz Garayev]].<ref name=CIA>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/world-leaders-1/world-leaders-a/azerbaijan.html |title=CIA. Chiefs of State and Cabinet Members of Foreign Governments |accessdate=2010-11-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100528054345/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/world-leaders-1/world-leaders-a/azerbaijan.html |archivedate=2010-05-28 |df= }}</ref>
==History== The ministry was established in May 1953 with a purpose of preservation, development, promotion of rich Azerbaijani culture and arts. The agency's included implementation of local and international cultural programs, projects and holding events in various countries. The objectives were to preserve and protect historical monuments and real estate, their renovation and use, modernization of libraries and museums, protection and promotion of [[Azerbaijani folklore]], development of cultural clubs, resorts and parks, revitalization of tourism, development of theater, musical and other forms of arts, revitalization of cinema and book publications and so forth.<ref name=Min>{{cite web |url=http://azerbaijan.tourism.az/index.php?/az/topmenu_content/1069 |title= Mədəniyyət və Turizm Nazirliyi |trans-title=Ministry of Culture and Tourism |accessdate=2010-11-01}}</ref>
==Organization== The ministry is headed by the minister with three deputy ministers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mct.gov.az/?/en/pers/505 |title= Ministry of Culture and Tourism of the Republic of Azerbaijan. Ministerial board |accessdate=2010-11-01}}</ref> Main functions of the ministry are implementation of state policies in the tourism sector and promotion of Azerbaijani culture, formulation and implementation of short-, mid- and long-term strategies and programs, increasing activities in cultural sector among the youth, create conditions for every citizen to contribute to the cultural development in Azerbaijan, increase production of Azerbaijani films, etc.<ref name=Min/>
==See also== *[[Cabinet of Azerbaijan]] *[[Tourism in Azerbaijan]] *[[Culture of Azerbaijan]] *[[Architecture of Azerbaijan]]
